<subSubSection box="[199,1310,1306,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="599" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,925,1364]" box="[199,1310,1306,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="599">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,327,1306,1329]" pageId="2" pageNumber="599">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[562,645,1306,1329]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Nirvanguina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectena">
<emphasis box="[562,645,1306,1329]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="599">pectena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” refers to the shape of the comblike pygofer dorsal processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1436,1341,1364]" pageId="2" pageNumber="599" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,925,1364]" box="[199,1436,1341,1364]" pageId="2" pageNumber="599">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,303,1341,1364]" pageId="2" pageNumber="599">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[586,697,1341,1364]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lamia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="599" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="placida">
<emphasis box="[586,697,1341,1364]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="599">N. placida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but can be distinguished in the male genitalia as indicated in the key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
